},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but that this is not a valid opinion: yet Suh and several others agree with Kr: pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"luyuwvN","text_ar":"لُيُوثٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and, as some say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maloyavapN","text_ar":"مَلْيَثَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$oyaxapN","text_ar":"مَشْيَخَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masoyafapN","text_ar":"مَسْيَفَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layovapN","text_ar":"لَيْثَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layovaAtN","text_ar":"لَيْثَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layovu","text_ar":"لَيْثُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eifir~iyna","text_ar":"عِفِرِّينَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The lion:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AA, S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an animal like the chameleon, that opposes itself to the rider;"},{"kind":"text","text":"so called in reference to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Efr~yn","text_ar":"عفرّين"},{"kind":"text","text":", the name of a town or district. (As, S.) One says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahu laA^a$ojaEu mino","text_ar":"اـِنَّهُ لَاَشْجَعُ مِنْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layovi Eifir~iyna","text_ar":"لَيْثِ عِفِرِّينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily he is more courageous than the lion, &c."},{"kind":"text","text":"] (S.) [See also art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Efr","text_ar":"عفر"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b4-  See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aloyavu","text_ar":"اَلْيَثُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layovN","text_ar":"لَيْثٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Eloquent:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strong in dispute:"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the dial. of Hudheyl. (TA.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"All~ayovu","text_ar":"اللَّيْثُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain kind of spider,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that hunts flies by leaping,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"springing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain kind of spider"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"surpassed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"equalled, by"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"no beast,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"creeping thing, in acuteness, and circumvention, and in leaping,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"springing, with correct aim, and in rapidity of snatching, and in dissimulation; that catches flies:"},{"kind":"text","text":"('Amr Ibn-Bahr:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the spider,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEanokabuwt","text_ar":"العَنْكَبُوت"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Lth:) or ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a reptile"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"smaller than the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Enkbwt","text_ar":"عنكبوت"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that catches flies."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layovN","text_ar":"لَيْثٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A land's having dry herbage, and being rained upon, and producing fresh herbage, so that half of it is green, and half of it yellow."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA","AA","Lth"]}]}}